caption: Had the buffalo wings today and they were AMAZING! I was grilling who i think is the owner wbout how i wanted my wings made (cause im a wing connoisseur) and he assured me he knew what he was doing then asked where i was from. I told him the Northside amd he proceeded to say Buffalo Joes has the best wings on the Northside (which is true... they really have the best wings EVER...until today) i got my wings and walked out and ate them in the car and INSTANTLY KNEW I FOUND SOMETHIMG BETTER THAN BUFFALO JOES. I came back with my gf and ordered 2 more orders and he was so nice enough to give me free fries on the house and even ran out our orders to our car!! The taste of the wings with the hospitality earns this man a 5 stars. Im big on respect and he did more than enough to make me feel like a valued customer on my first experience there. I LOVE these experiences
My favorite wings ever
They good they just lil then a mf so be aware .
Big high quality wings! Sauce isn’t necessarily that classic Buffalo flavor but it’s great in its own right. Combos well with ranch!
We love House of Wings!  Soooo perfect for Game Day!  Highly Recommend.
Ordered food yesterday, the service and food is great ! 👍
Crispy wings are the way to go. They could benefit from seasoning their fries a bit tho, meal just felt kind of simple for almost $14 (I go the 7 piece crispy wings and fries)

I don’t do reviews, but this place deserves one. My husband ordered some wings, and they are super crispy (just how I like them)!! This place met my expectations very well! On top of that the staff there were super friendly. I recommend this place for those crispy wing lovers.
Some of the best wings in Chicago

Nowhere close to the best wings in Chicago, as some other reviewers have suggested. The wings were somewhat dry, an issue exacerbated by the stinginess of the sauce. The buffalo was exceptionally bland, lacking the tang of even your neighborhood Frank’s Red backyard cookout wings, but the barbecue was slightly better. Neither had the complexity or flavor profile one would expect after eating at Jake Melnick’s or Crisp (two restaurants who could credibly claim the honor of best Chicago wings). Overall, the experience was standard bar fare - if passing this place late at night and by happenstance, I would gladly walk in and grab something to eat (likely a small serving of the barbecue wings, and then an unrelated menu item). But I wouldn’t suggest anyone uber or walk out of their way to come here.

These are the best wings I've ever had!  Order the extra crispy small and you won't be disappointed!   I grew up going to many of the "original buffalo wing" venues in Western New York and these wings are better!  Yes, they are expensive, but  you pay for the quality and the quality is amazing!
Ordered teriyaki wings.  Got wings with just sauce poured on. The wings aren't even seasoned.
Really good wings definitely  a must

BEST WINGS IN ALL OF CHICAGO! SUPER CRISPY AND PERFECT BITE SIZE WINGS! THE BUFFALO FLAVOR IS OUT IF THIS WORLD AND LIKE NO OTHER! ALSO THE STAFF MEMBERS ARE SUPER SWEET AND FRIENDLY. FOOD IS BOMB AND FAST AND ON TOP OF THAT THEY PROVIDE EXCELLENT SERVICE. XOXO ❤️🍗 #ONCEYOUEATTHESEWINGSYOUAINTGOINGNOWHEREELSEFORWINGS
Best wings I’ve ever had. The crispy option is amazing and the homemade buffalo is out of this world. Great quality meat too. Highly recommend
Best wings in Lincoln Park

Get the spicy buffalo breaded wings!  Yummmy in my tummmmy.  They are the best, perfectly seasoned, with a slight crispy crunch to them yet not too much breading.  Ahhh I love this place.  Owner and cook are so sweet as well :)

OK their wings are way too small they're like tiny wings I can't believe they actually have little chickens that are this tiny, lol. Not kidding,  You know the small packet of handy wipes the single little handy wipes they give you at a restaurant, well that's how big / little these wings are. Not very impressive.  And their prices are a little high especially for these little wings. High prices, little food, not for me. You might wanna go elsewhere for bigger meatier wings...

Great service, great food.  The people that work here are wonderful.  They are incredibly friendly and the food they make is amazing.  Some of their combinations like the ultra goliath sandwich are a bit out there but the food is always fantastic.
Perfect hole in the wall place, I've always gotten exactly what I expected or better. Burger and cheese fries, Philly beef with extra cheese, onion rings with a side of ranch...love it
This place is amazing food is always perfectly made 👍👍 so yes u should eat here
Prices are high, but they worth it! It's delicious like a lot! I love the crispy wings, really nice bufflalo sauce!
Fantastic wings! I recommend getting them crispy. It's a more expensive, but definitely worth it.
Wing were super tasteful and delicious.
First time going here and it was great! This is the best chicken in town that I went to. I honestly recommend it to everyone!
Good wings. Perfect

Tiny wings. I had them in high school and I remember them being way better. Some pieces were inedible. It’s very overpriced for the quality of the wings, I should’ve just went to BWW. Probably not going back here again.
I spent some time in western New York was I was young and the wings remind me of the original hot wings developed and perfected there
Very tasty chicken wings in this area.

DONT GO HERE! disgusting! the prices are over high, they don’t even serve meals. we order hot wings and bbq wings which were both so disgusting and one the hot wings weren’t hot and the bbq taste like teriyaki. the menu the put on google is not the one it is in real life. the food even caused one of ya to get food poisoning and was throwing up the whole next morning. i do NOT recommend.

Love House of Wings, whether you like them spicy or mild or breaded  this is a great place for wings. Great fish, and beef sandwiches too. Small sitting area is only drawback. Wish they had bigger restaurant. But take out and delivery service is available. Good service.

Okay I understand plump chicken wings are hard to come by nowadays and this place is no exception. A couple of small chairs and tables in case you need to eat on the run. The best thing about this place though is the super fast service.

Really enjoy the chicken sandwich here. Was my father's and I's favorite spot to go to in the area. Great and inexpensive as well!

If you're looking to satisfy the guilty pleasures your heart desires and haven't been to this hole in the wall, you do not know what you are missing. The hot buffalo wings are the way to go. As a purist I can't recommend the crispy breaded variety out of principle. Notable mention also goes out to the philly and buffalo sub.
best wings in lincoln park hands down very good size wings and the sauce is finger-licking gooooood!!! breaded mushrooms were delicious too bleu cheese was not available when we went..boo :(

Best wings in Chicago?  Try best wings anywhere!  Yes, they are not huge.  Get over it and order another dozen.  The extra crispy were as close to wing perfection as I've tasted.  I was traveling from Europe to Chicago for a business trip with a craving for wings--they haven't a clue over here.  I could have eaten anywhere in Chicago, but I'm glad I found this place.  I'll let my boss wonder about the $7.15 for dinner on my expense account.
